commit.message: Add "itk::build-info" command, if loaded in Tcl 8.7+
Update version -> 4.2.3
Add type-casts to Itcl_EventuallyFree(), fixing potential gcc compiler warnings

Version number -> 4.2.2 (matching Itcl)
Make it work with Tcl 9.0

Update to latest TEA.
Make itkConfig.sh work.
Closes [7bbf7d75a7].

Update to latest TEA. Improve tests/all.tcl.

This file used to be [https://core.tcl.tk/itk/finfo?name=configure.in]
Remove Mac OS 9 support.
Stop using obsolete [source -rsrc].
Repurpose the trunk for ongoing development of Itk 4.1.*.
Several revisions to get evaluation contexts more reliably correct.
Take care that the right commands are resolved in the right namespaces.
Similar changes to the PropagatePublicVariable machinery.

Attempt to make code say clearly what it does, instead of achieving so much
with namespace context games.

[6acb6a8363] When Itk_AddOptionPart() fails, be sure no remnant of the
failed attempt remains to lead to nasty double free.
Don't allow Itk 4.0.3 to bring in Itcl 4.1+, which will break it.
Bump to 4.1.0
Commit to the patch; code history is in code history.
merge trunk
Bump to Itk 4.0.3.
Support [return] in an itcl::configbody.
merge trunk
Protect against loading Itk 4 in an interp already housing Itcl 3.
merge trunk
Improvements to the MSVC build machinery and porting fixes to code from Ashok Nadkarni.
Removed some unnecessary quotes
Added some comments about building

Fixes for building with Visual C++ compilers. Tested
with VC++ 6 (32-bit) and 2003 SDK compiler (64-bit).

C sources changed to conform to C89 (instead of C99).
makefile.vc and nmakehlp.c updated (too many changes to list)
Build expects Itcl to reside in a directory called itcl that is
the sibling of the itk directory.
nmake install also works but nmake winhelp (docs) does not
as it relies on an external program hrtf.exe which I do
not have.

Only verified with the demo itkedit script after modifying
the Iwidgets package to use Itk 4 instead of Itk 3.
The test scripts fail with errors that I believe are not
related to Windows.
merge trunk
merge release
Bump to Itk 4.0.2
